ON CAMPUS
VISTA recruiting will be on
the Grinnell College campus, 36‘
working to assistant field director Debora Signorroci, on
October 23 and 24.
More than 75 per cent of
VISTA Volunteers are drawn
from college computer. This
year, VISTA will detroit and
train 4,500 Volunteers to serve
in more than 300 projects from
coast to coast and in Hawaii,
Alaska, Puerto Rico and the
virgin islands.
The projects are located in
urban sluts, rural areas, Indian reservations, warrant
camps, Job Corps centers and
mental hospitals. VISTA trainers may express a preference
for location and type oi as
alignment,
The V lunteers train intensive
ly for six weeks and serve for
one year. They receive a monthly allowance to cover basic lib<
' Ing expenses. At the end of ser-
vice, they receive a student or
$50 for each month served.
